                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 8.  <span>Hybridization analysis of 42 arrays demonstrating the sensitivity and linear dynamic range.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p1"></a><p>Each point represents the mean of the normalized probe intensities for the spike-in control transcripts across three arrays plotted against the concentration of spike-in control transcripts.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p2" name="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p2"></a><p>Error bars indicate the standard deviation across the three arrays at each data point.</p>
<a id="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p3" name="article1.body1.sec2.fig7.caption1.p3"></a><p>Spike-in control transcripts were added to a complex background of K-562 cRNA at 13 different concentrations ranging from 0.25 pM to 1024 pM (approximately 1:600,000 to 1:150 mass ratio) in two-fold increments.</p>
